<br>
Because there are not facial expressions or inflection of voice, part of the message gets lost in text.  Not to mention mis-reading, typos or wording things wrong.  <br>
<br>
I really think this thing got blown out of proportion when Vehnn informed Maniak that the Magi was dead and what he dropped.  <br>
<br>
Usually, when someone dies they are not happy.  If I got a comment such that Vehnn made (You told maniak, 'legs btw keke')--it can be interrepeted in a few ways (even more possilby):<br>
<br>
1)  I'm informing you what just dropped--it was rubbish.  <br>
2)  hehehe.  You got owned by the Magi, but it didn't drop anything.<br>
3)  (Hmmm...SMR dropped, but fuck I don't want them to know.)  Oh yah, it was nothing.  <br>
<br>
Remember, you are upset that you died to a Mob you shoulda killed that has the potential to drop a pretty nice piece of loot.  It is very possible you will overreact.  Then the person on the other side, especially if they were being helpful will get defensive if wrongly accused and will probably get aggressive back.  One thing leads to another...  <br>
<br>
I'm sorry that this incident happened.  I'm sorry it got to be this big.  I tried to control is before things got out of hand.  <br>
<br>
As for guildmates making posts.  I am not sayin what they said was correct or not, but I know that when one of my own gets attacked, I'm going to stand up for them.  Pretty much everyone defends their guildmates when something goes public like this.  If you don't stand up for your own &quot;family&quot;--who will?  <br>
<br>
I really hate arguments.  I really hate fighting among people/guilds/etc...  I hope people can be more patient with one another and try to act calmly and discuss things before blowing things up and posting and blah-blah-blah.  <br>
<br>
BTW--I find speaking with an officer/guild leader/fellow guildmate that you know is often a very effective way of rectifying a situation.  Arguing with the person you are having a dispute with will usually get you nowhere.  Talking to a third party or an authority in the organization you are trying to deal with may help things out.  (If you have a problem with any of peeps--feel free to give me a /tell if I'm on-line).  <br>
<br>
This is a stupid incident that was blown way out of proportion.  I'm sure there are other stupid things we can talk about--like my hairy feet or something.  <br>
<br>
Thank you for your time...<br>
<br>
--Bakxs<br>
